22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fdeny-defend-and-depose-detectives-uncover-new-evidences-in-unitedhealthcare-ceo-brian-thompsons-murder-case%2Famp_articleshow%2F115993750.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22France's%20Government%20Ousted%20In%20No-Confidence%20Vote.%20What%20Happens%20Next%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20in%20France%20collapsed%20on%20Wednesday%20after%20lawmakers%20of%20both%20left%20and%20right%20wings%20joined%20forces%20to%20push%20a%20no-confidence%20against%20the%20country's%20Prime%20Minister%20Michel%20Barnier%2C%20throwing%20the%20European%20Union's%20second-biggest%20economic%20power%20deeper%20into%20chaos%20that%20threatens%20to%20exacerbate%20its%20budgetary%20and%20looming%20economic%20crises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister%20addressed%20the%20nation%20just%20before%20the%20vote%2C%20calling%20it%20an%20honour%20to%20have%20served%20France%20and%20its%20people%20with%20dignity.%20He'd%20been%20on%20the%20job%20for%20just%20two%20months%20and%2029%20days.%20With%20the%20vote%20of%20confidence%20against%20him%2C%20Mr%20Barnie%20will%20now%20have%20to%20tender%20his%20resignation%20and%20that%20of%20his%20government%20to%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%2C%20making%20his%20minority%20government's%20tenure%20the%20shortest%20lived%20in%20France's%20Fifth%20Republic%20beginning%20in%201958.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20French%20media%20reports%2C%20he%20is%20expected%20to%20do%20so%20on%20Thursday%20morning.%20The%20president%20will%20then%20address%20the%20nation%20at%201900%20GMT%2C%20the%20Elysee%20Palace%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERise%20and%20Fall%20Of%20Michel%20Barnier%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMichel%20Barnier's%20government%20fell%20after%20331%20deputies%20voted%20against%20him%2C%20making%20him%20the%20shortest-serving%20Prime%20Minister%20in%20modern%20French%20political%20history.%20Only%20288%20votes%20were%20needed%20to%20pass%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20in%20the%20577-member%20chamber.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20successful%20no-confidence%20vote%20since%20a%20defeat%20for%20Georges%20Pompidou's%20government%20in%201962%2C%20when%20Charles%20de%20Gaulle%20was%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20France%2C%20the%20President%20nominates%20prime%20ministers.%20However%2C%20lawmakers%20can%20reject%20his%20picks%20at%20any%20time%20by%20passing%20a%20no-confidence%20vote%2C%20like%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Barnier.%20National%20Assembly%2C%20the%20French%20parliament's%20lower%20house%2C%20is%20almost%20equally%20divided%20between%20the%20far%20right%2C%20a%20loosely%20united%20left-wing%2C%20centrists%20including%20Macron's%20allies%2C%20and%20a%20few%20candidates%20who%20please%20all%20three%20factions%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fworld-politics%2F389827%2Ffrance-government-collapse-budget-economic-crisis-bernier-macron-le-pen%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVox%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20not%20a%20popular%20leader%2C%20Mr%20Barnier%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20capable%20choice%20after%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20post%20following%20surprise%20elections%20this%20past%20summer.%20However%2C%20he%20was%20met%20with%20challenges%20while%20trying%20to%20lead%20a%20government%20without%20a%20majority.%20He%20angered%20lawmakers%20on%20both%20the%20right%20and%20left%20after%20he%20attempted%20to%20push%20through%20a%202025%20national%20budget%20without%20a%20vote%20in%20the%20lower%20house%20of%20parliament.%20Amid%20a%20standoff%20over%20the%20social%20security%20financing%20bill%2C%20France's%20far-right%20party%20and%20its%20left-wing%20alliance%20each%20put%20forward%20no-confidence%20motions%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPassage%20of%20No%20Confidence%20Vote%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20successful%20vote%20means%20President%20Macron%20will%20have%20to%20find%20a%20new%20Prime%20Minister%20to%20replace%20Mr%20Barnier%2C%20which%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20be%20an%20easy%20affair.%20A%20similar%20situation%20happened%20once%20before%20in%201962%2C%20but%20the%20particular%20situation%20was%20dealt%20with%20by%20calling%20early%20legislative%20elections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20President%20Macron%20doesn't%20have%20that%20choice%20as%20he%20has%20already%20called%20called%20early%20poll%20last%20June.%20This%20means%20he%20can't%20call%20new%20ones%20until%20next%20July%2C%20because%20under%20the%20French%20Constitution%2C%20the%20National%20Assembly%20must%20remain%20in%20place%20for%20a%20minimum%20of%20one%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20for%20the%20moment%2C%20France%20has%20no%20government.%20However%2C%20it%20will%20have%20caretaker%20ministers%20in%20place%2C%20appointed%20by%20the%20President.%20Amid%20limited%20options%20given%20the%20dysfunction%20in%20the%20National%20Assembly%2C%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20needs%20to%20appoint%20a%20new%20prime%20minister%20quickly%20to%20pass%20the%20government's%20budget%20and%2C%20hopefully%2C%20prevent%20an%20economic%20crisis%20from%20engulfing%20France.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20source%20close%20to%20Macron%20told%20news%20agency%20AFP%20that%20the%20president%2C%20who%20has%20taken%20time%20with%20appointments%20in%20the%20past%2C%20has%20%26quot%3Bno%20choice%26quot%3B%20but%20to%20name%20the%20new%20premier%20within%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECall%20For%20Emmanuel%20Macron's%20Resignation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrance's%20hard%20left%20on%20Wednesday%20urged%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20to%20resign%20and%20hold%20early%20presidential%20elections%20after%20lawmakers%20voted%20to%20oust%20the%20government%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Michel%20Barnier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20now%20calling%20on%20Macron%20to%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20Mathilde%20Panot%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20parliamentary%20faction%20of%20the%20hard-left%20France%20Unbowed%20(LFI)%20party%20told%20reporters%2C%20urging%20%26quot%3Bearly%20presidential%20elections%26quot%3B%20to%20solve%20a%20deepening%20political%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20taking%20care%20not%20to%20crow%20over%20the%20government's%20fall%2C%20Le%20Pen%20said%20in%20a%20television%20interview%20that%20her%20party%20--%20once%20a%20new%20premier%20is%20appointed%20--%20%26quot%3Bwould%20let%20them%20work%26quot%3B%20and%20help%20create%20a%20%26quot%3Bbudget%20that%20is%20acceptable%20for%20everyone%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaurent%20Wauquiez%2C%20the%20head%20of%20right-wing%20deputies%20in%20parliament%2C%20said%20the%20far%20right%20and%20hard%20left%20bore%20the%20responsibility%20for%20a%20no-confidence%20vote%20that%20would%20%26quot%3Bplunge%20the%20country%20into%20instability%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMacron%2C%20however%2C%20has%20rejected%20calls%20to%20resign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrowing%20Crisis%20In%20France%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20markets%20nervous%20and%20France%20bracing%20for%20public-sector%20strikes%20against%20the%20threat%20of%20cutbacks%2C%20action%20that%20will%20shut%20schools%20and%20hit%20air%20and%20rail%20traffic%2C%20there%20is%20a%20growing%20sense%20of%20crisis.%20The%20unions%20have%20called%20for%20civil%20servants%2C%20including%20teachers%20and%20air-traffic%20controllers%2C%20to%20strike%20on%20Thursday%20over%20separate%20cost-cutting%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20Macron%20is%20due%20to%20host%20a%20major%20international%20event%20on%20Saturday%2C%20with%20the%20reopening%20of%20the%20Notre-Dame%20Cathedral%20after%20the%202019%20fire%2C%20with%20guests%20including%20Donald%20Trump%20on%20his%20first%20foreign%20trip%20since%20he%20was%20elected%20to%20be%20the%20next%20US%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrance%20also%20risks%20ending%20the%20year%20without%20a%20stable%20government%20or%20a%202025%20budget%2C%20although%20the%20constitution%20allows%20special%20measures%20that%20would%20avert%20a%20US-style%20government%20shutdown.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20new%20prime%20minister%20appointed%20by%20the%20President%20would%20face%20the%20same%20challenges%20as%20Barnier%20in%20getting%20bills%2C%20including%20the%202025%20budget%2C%20adopted%20by%20a%20divided%20parliament.%20Macron%20could%20alternatively%20ask%20Barnier%20and%20his%20ministers%20to%20stay%20on%20in%20a%20caretaker%20capacity%20while%20he%20takes%20time%20to%20identify%20a%20prime%20minister%20able%20to%20attract%20sufficient%20cross-party%20support%20to%20pass%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20caretaker%20government%20could%20either%20propose%20emergency%20legislation%20to%20roll%20the%20tax-and-spend%20provisions%20in%20the%202024%20budget%20into%20next%20year%20or%20invoke%20special%20powers%20to%20pass%20the%20draft%202025%20budget%20by%20decree%20-%20though%20jurists%20say%20this%20is%20a%20legal%20grey%20area%20and%20the%20political%20cost%20would%20be%20huge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20potentially%20cause%20further%20concerns%20in%20markets%2C%20which%20are%20already%20unnerving%20investors%20in%20French%20sovereign%20bonds%20and%20stocks.%20Earlier%20this%20week%2C%20France's%20borrowing%20costs%20briefly%20exceeded%20those%20of%20Greece%2C%20generally%20considered%20far%20more%20risky.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrance's%20political%20turmoil%20also%20threatens%20to%20weaken%20a%20European%20Union%20already%20reeling%20from%20the%20implosion%20of%20Germany's%20coalition%20government%2C%20weeks%20before%20US%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20returns%20to%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country's%20outgoing%20defence%20minister%20Sebastien%20Lecornu%20warned%20the%20turmoil%20could%20impact%20French%20support%20for%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733378040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Ffp3rvmng_french-p