29-400x300.jpeg%20400w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-11-27-at-2.30.09-PM-1_11zon-1732714129-200x150.jpeg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-11-27-at-2.30.09-PM-1_11zon-1732714129-150x112.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-383606%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221805%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWildlife%20watering%20hole%20inspired%20by%20Tal%20Chhapar%20Sanctuary%2C%20Nagaur%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20fund%20their%20work%20long-time%2C%20Sharvan%20and%20his%20team%20started%20a%20WhatsApp%20group%20called%2C%20%E2%80%98One%20Rupee%20Per%20Day%20for%20Wildlife%20Conservation%E2%80%99.%20The%20idea%20was%20that%20if%20people%20were%20financially%20invested%20in%20the%20cause%2C%20they%20would%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20stay%20engaged%20and%20involved.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20around%201%2C000%20members%20in%20the%20group%2C%20and%20they%20pay%20Rs%20365%20every%20year%20for%20wildlife%20conservation%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sharvan%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20has%20helped%20us%20raise%20funds%20for%20plantation%20efforts%2C%20filling%20up%20watering%20holes%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F299651%2Fconservationist-meera-chandran-quit-job-to-fight-invasive-plant-species-restore-forest-land%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremoval%20of%20invasive%20species.%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20grassroots%20efforts%2C%20Sharvan%20has%20made%20smart%20use%20of%20social%20media%20to%20amplify%20his%20cause%20and%20engage%20with%20a%20larger%20audience.%20His%20Instagram%20page%2C%20%E2%80%98Thar%20Desert%20Photography%E2%80%99%2C%20has%20become%20a%20platform%20for%20raising%20awareness%20about%20the%20issues%20facing%20wildlife%20in%20the